      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Al-Arqam's financial model is characterized by its ability to generate <cite id=\"11\">$3,925,159 in program service revenue</cite>, largely through tuition, which covers the bulk of its <cite id=\"12\">$3,301,210 in total expenses</cite>. This self-sustaining model allows <cite id=\"13\">contributions of $224,548</cite> to be used with <cite id=\"7\">zero fundraising costs</cite>. Furthermore, the school demonstrates strong governance with a <cite id=\"14\">100% independent board of directors</cite>, ensuring objective oversight of its mission to meet the <cite id=\"15\">educational needs of Muslim children</cite> in Sacramento."
      ],
      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">1998</cite>, Al-Arqam Islamic School & College Preparatory serves the Greater Sacramento area by providing a <cite id=\"2\">comprehensive college preparatory curriculum</cite> integrated with Islamic studies. The institution is distinguished as an <cite id=\"3\">International Baccalaureate (IB) World School</cite>, offering the rigorous Diploma Programme designed to foster global citizenship. Financially, the school operates with high efficiency, reporting <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $4,155,519</cite> in 2023, with a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 98.1%</cite>. This indicates that all functional expenses are directed toward its educational mission. The school maintains a strong financial position with <cite id=\"6\">9.1 months of working capital</cite> and a <cite id=\"7\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 per $1 raised</cite>, ensuring that sadaqah contributions are utilized entirely for student services and school operations. Beyond academics, the school implements a <cite id=\"8\">Student Honor Code of Conduct</cite> and a House System to build character and community among its youth.",
